metadata.name: Euphonic #1149
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

Licensing: BY-NC-ND see license.md for details.

metadata.name: Rhythms #209
metadata.description:
"Routines, patterns, cadence.
Events, turns, chaos.
Predictable lives,
split-second dramas."

This project is inspired by the delicate balance between daily habits and life-turning points.
There's structure in the flow. There's awe in the silence.

"Rhythms" invites you to reflect on the beautiful complexity that fills our vital experience, on the millions of tiny details that bring texture to our journey causing balance or disruption.

-

Key Features:
- 12 color palettes: Determines colors used on the artwork
- 3 Orientation modes (square, portrait, landscape): Portrait and landscape are rare
- 6 Alignment Types: Determines lines' distribution pattern

Secondary features provide additional variation.

Enter live mode and press "s" to download high resolution image ( 5940x5940 px ).

-

50% of secondary market royalties go to minters.
Coded in p5js, with love.

metadata.name: Shapes #33
metadata.description:
While I was waiting for my turn in a doctor appointment, I saw a 'geometric-ish' framed art hanged in the wall of the waiting room. Those piece was so simple, but in the same time so elegant and this have inspired me a bit. So, I decided to make something similar using javascript, but with the fancy touch of randomization, tks to fxrand() function.

The supply is medium but the price is promotion.
Made with love.

D.

May 2022.

metadata.name: Chord Unknown #364
metadata.description:
The feeling of experimenting with an instrument you have not learned, and then suddenly striking an actual chord.

The code creates several grids and then applies one of six unique deformation techniques with varying intensity. It's a defined process of experimentation, and even though I'm the one that wrote the rules, each output breaks through somehow as a complete surprise to me. So when I see them, I get a Chord Unknown.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: Unbalanced Life #45
metadata.description:
Most of the time we don't know what we do with our lives, we try hard and make decisions hoping for the best. We could go from a balanced and well-directed life to a disastrous and shattered one.

"Unbalanced Life" is an abstraction of these aspects. Each line represents a stage in your life. Over each line are "life decisions" that you take. Several are well defined, others are just a mess and explode, like in real life! 

The life type will be included below in the right corner unless your life is seriously "Shattered", then the name will be huge enough to punch you right in the face, or you could get "No Life" and with that, a disappointing tag will remember you that at less your life is better than this NFT.

What kind of life will you get?

You will face these challenging features:

Life types
- Shattered life
- Unbalanced life
- Balanced life
- Wasted life
- Lack of life
- No life 

Four color schemes
- Groovy seventies
- Rad 80's
- Fire and fury
- Outstanding carbon

Well-thought decisions
- Boolean

metadata.name: Tesseract #226
metadata.description:
'Tesseract' is a generative collection drawing on the concept of the cube from oneirology, the interpretation of dreams. In many mythologies and fields of study, the square is considered a 'perfect shape', thus with its abstraction into three isometric dimensions, the cube is seen by some as a representation of the various aspects of the human condition.

In 'Tesseract', the ribbons flowing between the cubes represent the shared experiences that connect us all. No matter how different our lives might be, we all go through the same joys, sorrows, trials, tribulations and experience attachments of varying degrees. 

It is these experiences that bind us together and make us who we are. With these concepts in mind, viewers are invited to interpret each composition as it relates to them and their unique story, from the perspective of that which has been and that which is yet to be experienced.

Press 'S' to save a high resolution PNG at 2400 x 3396 px.
